55.1	Saadi_(poet)	Saadi (poet)	Abū-Muḥammad Muṣliḥ al-Dīn bin Abdallāh Shīrāzī, Saadi Shirazi (Persian: ‎) better known by his pen-name as Saʿdī (Persian: ‎) or, simply, Saadi, was one of the major Persian poets of the medieval period. He is not only famous in Persian-speaking countries, but he has also been quoted in western sources. He is recognized for the quality of his writings, and for the depth of his social and moral thoughts.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/36/Sadi_in_a_Rose_garden.jpg/220px-Sadi_in_a_Rose_garden.jpg
